The comparison is between such fields and Valgius' countenance.

2. mare Caspium: the stormy character of this sea is mentioned by Mela 3, 5 mare Caspium omne atrox, saevum, sine portubus, pro- cellis undique expositum. It is probable. however, that Horace's choice of this concrete example and of Armeniis in oris (cf. n. to 1, 1. 14) was determined by the coming reference to Augustus' successful diplomacy in the East (vv. 20—24).
